Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.97,0:03:11.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,Minoru Kijima (30)\NMakeup Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:17.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,Jiro Ishikawa (28)\NPhotographer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:23.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yoko Nakamura (25)\NFashion Model
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:54.32,Signs,,0,0,0,,Masataka Shimizu (25)\NPart-Time Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:02.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\i1}Conan{\i0} is approaching its tenth anniversary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.70,0:00:04.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\q2}And once we make it through the first decade,\Nlet's aim for another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.40,0:00:07.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A costume party takes an unexpected\Ntwist and becomes a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.96,0:00:09.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the sad tale behind a clown!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.96,0:00:11.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.46,0:00:13.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.46,0:00:15.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.76,0:02:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NPretty cool, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.50,0:02:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I assume you're familiar with the Animeland theme park.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.76,0:02:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They asked me to be the director for a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any point in doing it without a twist,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I figured I'd give it a personal touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that surprise was a big hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.23,0:02:18.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'll be the honorary director for a day next year again,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and every other year after.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come and rent a costume off you, so make sure you stay in business!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.18,0:02:29.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't remember them saying anything like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.80,0:02:34.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Didn't he see how shocked everyone was at how weird he was being?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.22,0:02:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess this will do. I'll give it to you as a present, signed and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's no need...\NWait, were you dancing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was\Nan earthquake at about 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was pretty strong, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.83,0:03:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to be directors for a day, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're going to a party,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.90,0:03:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to celebrate these two getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.96,0:03:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, a costume party?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.46,0:03:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a bit embarrassing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.76,0:03:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\q2}but someone said a normal party would be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.73,0:03:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we couldn't really argue with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since she's pretty influential.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.22,0:03:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A smile in your face,\Nand tears in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The makeup hides the tears,\Njust like with clowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops, I forgot my hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.98,0:03:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of costume\Nshould I wear next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.69,0:03:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one? No, maybe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.95,0:03:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one in charge of the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The earthquake shook me up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.53,0:03:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the preparations for the party are still underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.50,0:03:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder, the editor-in-chief hates earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.86,0:03:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says this is the costume she's wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.20,0:03:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This is Umeda, our editor-in-chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.92,0:04:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprise! Don't I look great?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got an e-mail from Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.73,0:04:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says she'll leave the door unlocked,\Nand we should come in as soon as we arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.01,0:04:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.76,0:04:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 4:30pm, so we'll get there\Nat 5pm sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A party, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go play pachinko and then get something tasty to eat, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you look after this\Nfor us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.53,0:04:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:43.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Get something tasty to eat, my foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You splurged everything you had playing pachinko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people are heartless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.70,0:04:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with picking up the balls somebody else dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.35,0:04:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The world's turning more\Nand more miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.00,0:04:55.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who's more miserable, the world or you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, an e-mail with a photo of a woman dressed up as a clown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.12,0:05:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on that girl's\Nmobile phone at 4:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.20,0:05:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is extreme pressure on the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, strangulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.36,0:05:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm certain of it, this is the woman we saw in that e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.96,0:05:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} saw an e-mail from the victim at 4:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corpse was found at 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.60,0:05:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking all the information into account,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.16,0:05:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we can say she was killed between 4:30pm and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what information?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! Stop bothering\Npeople with questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.12,0:05:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, please don't mind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.06,0:05:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:06:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a person dies,\Ntheir muscles stiffen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis, right?\NI read about it in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body usually stiffens up about two hours after death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's outside during a summer day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.56,0:06:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or in a warm place like here, where the heating's on,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.13,0:06:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it stiffens up faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But her body doesn't seem to have stiffened up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I can conclude
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:26.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that it hasn't been long since she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's 5:30 now, we can conclude she died just after 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who was Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?\NDo you know anything about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.30,0:06:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a talented editor-in-chief for a women's fashion magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who found the body,\Nis a famous makeup artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the victim was the one who discovered him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and helped him become who he is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was with her,\Nis a photographer for the same magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's also Yoko Nakamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who worked as a model.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.40,0:07:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's rings and necklaces are all missing from her jewellery box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could the young man we saw earlier have stolen them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.03,0:07:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they reached this block of flats,\Nthese two saw a suspicious man running off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.37,0:07:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw him at the entrance, just after parking the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.86,0:07:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing\Na black leather jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.28,0:07:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.55,0:07:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He looked like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.01,0:07:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe he was a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say that, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.97,0:07:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good evening, editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's so warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.60,0:07:48.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It feels really nice, coming from the cold outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.97,0:07:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.69,0:07:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Footprints? No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor! There are\Nfootprints in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.53,0:08:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We mustn't tamper with the footprints. The phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! He cut the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.14,0:08:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't bring my mobile phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the editor's?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.65,0:08:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know where it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, let's split up and look for a public phone to call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't leave\NYoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} here alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, they went off to search for a public phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.91,0:08:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hard, but we eventually found one in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They called 110 at 5:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got here at 5:30, and saw that Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:09:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how come neither of you were carrying a mobile phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.93,0:09:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had hers before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.53,0:09:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't bother people with questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though to be honest, I was about to ask the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We left our mobile phones at the costume shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hated mobile phones, since wherever she was, she'd get hounded by calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Particularly during parties, she would forbid anyone from bringing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she told me not to e-mail her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.46,0:09:28.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, you could find public phones anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.63,0:09:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but these days, they're a lot more scarce. What a strange time we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we're\Nbetter off or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.34,0:09:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, whether the killer knew it or whether it was a mere coincidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.44,0:09:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the fact is somebody broke into this unlocked house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.51,0:10:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was so focused on the preparations that she didn't notice the killer lying in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:08.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was attacked from the back while she was laying down the cutlery here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.97,0:10:11.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If somebody came in through that hallway, she'd have noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.38,0:10:14.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And she'd have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:23.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there are no signs of a struggle in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is this room identical\Nto how you found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:30.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remind me of a mystery series I watch on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.31,0:10:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.99,0:10:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's him, it's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the man we saw running away from the block of flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.03,0:10:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw him in the park in front of the station looking pretty nervous,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.00,0:10:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I decided to interrogate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he tried to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I caught him right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was carrying this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:11:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, can you show this to Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The footprints even match his shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.31,0:11:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.44,0:11:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were her favourite jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.56,0:11:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Please wait here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.57,0:11:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were asked to do it over the Internet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got a really interesting request.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The job consisted of\Ncoming here at 5pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.17,0:11:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,taking the jewellery on top of the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.86,0:11:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and taking it to the park in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop making up stories!\NYou killed her for money, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! When I got here, that clown was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran away because I didn't want to get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, this guy's pretty stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.35,0:11:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.68,0:11:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that instead of running away from the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.60,0:11:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he stayed around the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.85,0:11:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe somebody did hire him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.22,0:12:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being a theme park's director for a day is exhausting...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm getting sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:09.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh geez, he actually fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:18.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Beef stew?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.93,0:12:26.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's cold. The stove's been out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.97,0:12:29.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But according to the stove knob, it should be on low flame...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective, please! You have to believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.28,0:12:33.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.39,0:12:35.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.73,0:12:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.57,0:12:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s going to get started soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.73,0:12:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:47.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's not starting anything, he's sleeping for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:49.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, do you know what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.57,0:12:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the maintenance company in charge of this block of flats,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.26,0:13:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they told me it's an earthquake detector for the gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An earthquake detector?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.05,0:13:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.57,0:13:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a device that cuts off the gas distribution when there's an earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted one installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.73,0:13:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It cuts off the gas when there's a strong earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.84,0:13:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably cut off from the 3pm earthquake, and she forgot to light up the stove again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:20.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did she forget to light up the stove again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.35,0:13:23.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No... What if was she unable to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:26.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was probably already dead by the time the earthquake hit at 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:30.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the approximate time of death is between 4:30 and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.80,0:13:36.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she died before 3pm,\Nrigor mortis would've set in by 5:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.44,0:13:39.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}when Inspector Megure\Nand the others arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:42.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The heating was on,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.02,0:13:44.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so rigor mortis\Nshould've set in even faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:47.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that wasn't the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:49.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So what {\i1}did{\i0} happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.28,0:13:51.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That would mean she was left somewhere cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:56.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.57,0:13:58.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But there aren't many cold places in an ordinary house like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:05.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To slow down rigor mortis...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you need any help finding it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, don't worry. I'll get it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.66,0:14:23.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's not enough space under the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.04,0:14:25.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the closet wouldn't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.48,0:14:35.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there a ladder in this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.23,0:14:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ladder? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.75,0:14:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, there's one on the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used it last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.86,0:14:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the balcony? Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:54.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Grey makeup? It's fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brrr, it's cold!\NConan, where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:11.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Artificial hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:13.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There was no need for a ladder...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.95,0:15:15.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know who the killer is! {hannin wa ano hito! –Puto}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Detective!\NPlease believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.55,0:15:34.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. You came here, but didn't kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.51,0:15:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll hear the rest at HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.91,0:15:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.12,0:15:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, can we go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. By all means, feel free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.46,0:15:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The costume party was a complete wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.40,0:15:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even worse, you lost an important person to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fell asleep again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.82,0:16:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that was a rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now witness, as Sleeping Kogoro solves the most complicated of cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.00,0:16:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'm sorry, but we can't allow you to leave yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.25,0:16:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.88,0:16:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at what time did you meet Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.21,0:16:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 3pm, in front of\NBeika Department Store.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, before 3pm, where were you and what were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.95,0:16:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds like you want to confirm my alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.68,0:16:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's indeed the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.26,0:16:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who you just took away, is not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.23,0:16:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who killed Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.33,0:16:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was with us the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have time to kill the editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.17,0:17:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only time he wasn't with us was when we went to look for a public phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.11,0:17:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the editor was already dead by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed long before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, before you even met up with Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the approximate time of death is between 4:30 and 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.93,0:17:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, didn't you see the e-mail from Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That only means that Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mobile phone was used,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.84,0:17:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,not necessarily that she sent the e-mail herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.36,0:17:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the rigor mortis hadn't set in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.37,0:17:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body wasn't in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.31,0:17:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hid it in a cold place before you arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to delay rigor mortis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.75,0:17:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.73,0:17:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw her body at the same time as those two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:18:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, what was that dead clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.43,0:18:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.47,0:18:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A doll with clown makeup,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.35,0:18:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a similar stature to Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who suggested that today should be a costume party in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.04,0:18:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did she tell you that herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us the editor had suggested it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.13,0:18:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know that this floor's gas setup has an earthquake detection device?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earthquake?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Sato, can you bring the cooking pot here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.35,0:18:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us what's inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she was making beef stew,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's not cooked yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she'd left it as it was, I doubt it'd be ready on time for the party at 5pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.11,0:19:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was setting everything up so it was ready in time for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof of that, the stove's flame had been set to low.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She intended to have it cooked on time for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because of the earthquake detector, the stove went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never turned the gas back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she {\i1}couldn't{\i0} turn it back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why? Because she was already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have no evidence!\NThis is ridiculous, I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is {\i1}not{\i} done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, before meeting up with Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.32,0:19:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you came here and strangled Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho was setting everything up for the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you switched her body with a doll you'd set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.21,0:19:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.55,0:19:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you had to leave Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body somewhere cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.76,0:20:01.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to have everyone believe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:03.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that she was murdered shortly before the three of you arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.93,0:20:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you couldn't leave the body in a room with the heating on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you left without turning off the gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.88,0:20:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you wanted to ensure that the beef stew was ready
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,once you found Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.60,0:20:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately for you, there was an earthquake around 3pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.02,0:20:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the gas was stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.70,0:20:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not knowing that, you went shopping
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.48,0:20:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went off to the costume shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.26,0:20:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with Umeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nphone that you'd stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.02,0:20:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you sent that e-mail to make it look like she was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.87,0:20:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, you made sure everyone left their phones there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.44,0:20:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon finding the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you asked Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to look for a public phone with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.84,0:20:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you knew Ishikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would never leave his girlfriend alone with a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you'd be in this flat, under\Napparently normal circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.17,0:21:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you took\NUmeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s real body,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which you'd hidden\Non the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ditched the doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.53,0:21:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that moment, the grey clown makeup stained the balcony's curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.28,0:21:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're lying!\NYou're making it all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.42,0:21:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have no evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.63,0:21:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come out to the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.34,0:21:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kijima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this is your car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.71,0:21:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.61,0:21:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman deserved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.15,0:21:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that she made me who I am today,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.24,0:21:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but every time I found a girlfriend, she'd always step in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me that if I ever broke up with her,\Nshe'd make sure I'd never find work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.66,0:22:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just like a clown,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.02,0:22:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,always hiding my true feelings under a veil of makeup!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.48,0:23:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire chief for a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.94,0:23:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man never changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.26,0:23:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, is this going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:23:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.26,0:24:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The transmitter's signal disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.42,0:24:11.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They're going to assassinate someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.20,0:24:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man's in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.38,0:24:16.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just 90 metres...\NI have to make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.85,0:24:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara, do you know anything?\NWho's DJ?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:32.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan special:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.49,0:24:37.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.49,0:24:37.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,A transmitter and a bug
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.24,0:24:39.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, it's the tenth anniversary...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.12,0:24:40.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,...special!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.36,0:24:42.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At last, the Black Organisation!
